Sentencas: NiCu-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-delta based cermets are evaluated as anode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) using hydrocarbon fuels.
Titulo: NiCu-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-δ anode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: Polarization curves and stability tests are conducted for direct methane SOFCs with various anode materials at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: NiCu-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-δ anode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: The performances and thermal stabilities of the cells with Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-delta based anodes are significantly higher than those using pure CeO2-based anodes, indicating by doping 10 mol% Zr into CeO2, the thermal stability and anode performance can be improved.
Titulo: NiCu-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-δ anode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: Among the anode materials investigated, the best performing anode is Ni-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-delta.
Titulo: NiCu-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-δ anode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: The cell using the Ni0.5Cu0.5-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-delta anode exhibits a similar performance to that with the Ni-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-delta 5 anode, but experiences a much lower degradation after a short-term operation in weakly humidified CH4.
Titulo: NiCu-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-δ anode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: The cell using the Cu-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-delta anode shows the best stability, only 0.61% degradation after a 48 h operation, but a low performance as well.
Titulo: NiCu-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-δ anode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: The results suggest that NiCu-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-delta based cermets could be promising candidate anodes for direct hydrocarbon IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: NiCu-Zr0.1Ce0.9O2-δ anode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells using hydrocarbon fuels
